-- CIBC Appoints Suzann Pennington Chief Investment Officer
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-05-17T18:16:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-17/cibc-appoints-suzann-pennington-chief-investment-officer.html
(Corrects Geist’s title in third pargraph.)  Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce
promoted Suzann Pennington to chief investment officer of its
asset management business and hired Stephen Carlin as vice
president and senior portfolio manager of Canadian equities.  Pennington, who joined the Toronto-based firm in May 2011,
was head of Canadian equities and Carlin was head of Canadian
equities at Aegon Capital Management Inc., which manages C$8.5
billion ($8.5 billion).  “These appointments further strengthen our ability to
deliver superior investment results and manage risk for our
clients,” said Steve Geist, chief executive officer and
president of CIBC Global Asset Management, in a statement today.  The  money manager  for  Canada ’s fifth-biggest bank has more
than C$80 billion in assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
